    "final_text": "```python\nfrom build123d import *\n\n# Deterministic visual-hull reconstruction from orthographic silhouettes.\n# The part is reconstructed by intersecting three prisms derived from the \n# front, top, and right view profiles.\n\nsize_x = 135.664453\nsize_y = 72.162142\nsize_z = 8.942643\n\n# Front view profile (XZ plane)\nfront_pts = [\n    (135.664453, 0.000000),\n    (0.264453, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 8.679624),\n    (135.664453, 8.942643),\n]\n\n# Top view profile (XY plane)\ntop_pts = [\n    (135.664453, 0.000000),\n    (0.264453, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 71.898134),\n    (135.664453, 72.162142),\n]\n\n# Right view profile (YZ plane)\nright_pts = [\n    (72.162142, 0.000000),\n    (0.140667, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 8.801444),\n    (72.162142, 8.942643),\n]\n\ndef prism_from_profile(points, plane, amount):\n    \"\"\"Creates a prism by extruding a polygon defined by points on a given plane.\"\"\"\n    with BuildSketch(plane) as sketch:\n        Polygon(*points)\n    return extrude(sketch.sketch.face(), amount=amount)\n\n# Create the three prisms and intersect them to find the common volume.\n# The prisms are positioned to align their extents.\nfront = Pos(size_x / 2.0, size_y, size_z / 2.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    front_pts, Plane.XZ, amount=size_y\n)\ntop = Pos(size_x / 2.0, size_y / 2.0, 0.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    top_pts, Plane.XY, amount=size_z\n)\nright = Pos(0.0, size_y / 2.0, size_z / 2.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    right_pts, Plane.YZ, amount=size_x\n)\n\n# The final part is the intersection of the three prisms.\npart = (front & top) & right\n```",
    "code": "from build123d import *\n\n# Deterministic visual-hull reconstruction from orthographic silhouettes.\n# The part is reconstructed by intersecting three prisms derived from the \n# front, top, and right view profiles.\n\nsize_x = 135.664453\nsize_y = 72.162142\nsize_z = 8.942643\n\n# Front view profile (XZ plane)\nfront_pts = [\n    (135.664453, 0.000000),\n    (0.264453, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 8.679624),\n    (135.664453, 8.942643),\n]\n\n# Top view profile (XY plane)\ntop_pts = [\n    (135.664453, 0.000000),\n    (0.264453, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 71.898134),\n    (135.664453, 72.162142),\n]\n\n# Right view profile (YZ plane)\nright_pts = [\n    (72.162142, 0.000000),\n    (0.140667, 0.000000),\n    (0.000000, 8.801444),\n    (72.162142, 8.942643),\n]\n\ndef prism_from_profile(points, plane, amount):\n    \"\"\"Creates a prism by extruding a polygon defined by points on a given plane.\"\"\"\n    with BuildSketch(plane) as sketch:\n        Polygon(*points)\n    return extrude(sketch.sketch.face(), amount=amount)\n\n# Create the three prisms and intersect them to find the common volume.\n# The prisms are positioned to align their extents.\nfront = Pos(size_x / 2.0, size_y, size_z / 2.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    front_pts, Plane.XZ, amount=size_y\n)\ntop = Pos(size_x / 2.0, size_y / 2.0, 0.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    top_pts, Plane.XY, amount=size_z\n)\nright = Pos(0.0, size_y / 2.0, size_z / 2.0) * prism_from_profile(\n    right_pts, Plane.YZ, amount=size_x\n)\n\n# The final part is the intersection of the three prisms.\npart = (front & top) & right",
